  "texts": [
    "In a minimal extension allowing for neutrino masses and mixing, they can occur at rates much smaller than the present experimental upper bounds discussed below.",
    "We then turn to the µ -→ e -conversion in nuclei.• µ -→ e -γIn a version of the SM extended with the see-saw mechanism to describe massive neutrinos this process can occur through a penguin diagram with internal W and oscillating neutrinos.",
    "The photon is emitted by W. If there is a Z ′ with LFV couplings, other penguin diagrams contribute, with Z ′ and a charged lepton in the loop.",
    "The branching fraction is [62] B(µ → eγ) = 3(4π) 3 α 4G 2 F |A M eµ | 2 + |A E eµ | 2,(62)whereA M eµ = - 1 96π 2 M 2 Z ′ f =e,µ,τ ∆ f e * V ∆ f µ V 1 -3 m f m µ + ∆ f e * A ∆ f µ A 1 + 3 m f m µ,(63)A E eµ = i 96π 2 M 2 Z ′ f =e,µ,τ ∆ f e * A ∆ f µ V 1 -3 m f m µ + ∆ f e * V ∆ f µ A 1 + 3 m f m µ,(64)and∆ ij V and ∆ ij A defined as ∆ ij V = ∆ ij R + ∆ ij L, ∆ ij A = ∆ ij R -∆ ij L.(65)The sum in ( 63),( 64) is over the charged leptons in the loop.• ℓ j → ℓ i ll ℓ kIn the see-saw extended SM these modes are also described by loop diagrams, either penguins or boxes.",
    "In the ABCD model a tree-level diagram contributes with Z ′ as mediator."
  ],
